subtitleNullable: World Press Freedom Index 2014 to 2023 by by Reporters Without Borders (RSF)
descriptionNullable:
**Overview**
The World Press Freedom Index assesses the state of journalism in 180 countries and territories, highlights the disastrous effects of news and information chaos – the effects of a globalized and unregulated online information space that encourages fake news and propaganda. Press Freedom is the fundamental principle that communication and expression through various media, including printed and electronic media, especially published materials, should be considered a right to be exercised freely.

**Original Source**
The data collected from [https://rsf.org/en/index](rsf.org) on September 2023

**Data**
This dataset consists of reports from 2014 to 2023. Each file contains country ranking and score.
